cinnamon.engine.utils

Class IntStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • cinnamon.engine.utils.IntStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Copier<IntStack>, Iterable<Integer>

    public final class IntStack
extends Object
implements Copier<IntStack>, Iterable<Integer>

    Array-backed stack of primitive ints. This class is meant to replace stacking ints with generic classes when operations are expected to be frequent and repeated instantiation through autoboxing at high frequency is to be avoided.

    For compatibility with the Iterable interface, the Iterator returned by this class' iterator() method autoboxes.

    Growth

    The IntStack's internal array grows automatically when full and the amount of growth can be controlled by the growth factor passed during construction. However, the array is not automatically shrunken. To do so, compact() must manually be called in order to allow the potentially blocking operation to execute at appropriate times.

      • IntStack

        public IntStack(int initialCapacity,
                float growth,
                int... values)

        Constructs an IntStack with a specific initial capacity, normalized growth factor, and values. If the given initial capacity is smaller than the number of given values, the value count is instead taken as the initial capacity.

        Parameters:
        initialCapacity - initial capacity before growth.
        growth - factor to grow capacity by (must be > 0 and <= 1).
        values - starting stack content.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if initial capacity is <= 0, growth is <= 0 or > 1, or the number of starting values is 0.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object obj)

        Returns true if either the given object is the same IntStack or the following conditions are met.

        • The given object is also an IntStack.
        • Both IntStacks have the same size.
        • Each int a is equivalent to an int b in the other stack such that a.equals(b).
        • Both ints in an equivalent pair have the same positions in their respective stacks.
